---
title: Pan-Seared Chicken with Herbs De Provence Over a Warm Farro, Mozzarella, and Tomato Jumble
description: Between France’s bistro fare and Italy’s trattoria eats, it’s hard to say which country has the supreme cuisine. In fact, we love both so much that we’re tempted to make a hybrid out of the two and call it Fritalian. So say hello to our border-hopping recipe, which features both chicken seasoned with herbs de Provence (southern France’s trademark seasoning) and a farro caprese that is loaded with classic Italian ingredients, like tomatoes, mozzarella, and balsamic vinegar.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w13-r1-a322796a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w13-r1-2d0380cc.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 38 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 57 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 390 mg
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pan-seared-chicken-with-herbs-de-provence-589ca9cb51d3f15df4662ce3
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
cuisine: North America
---

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Bring 2⅓ cups water and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Once boiling, add @farro{1/2%cup} and shallot. Lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> TIP: If there is still water in pot after cooking, drain farro and return to pot.

Wash and dry all produce. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz} lengthwise. Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into small cubes.

With your hand on top of one @chicken breasts{12%oz}, cut ¾ of the way, parallel to #cutting board{}, stopping before you slice through completely. Open it up like a book. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}, and @herbes de Provence{1%tablespoon}. Repeat with remaining chicken breast.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}, @honey{1/2%oz}, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add chicken in a single layer. Cook until browned and no longer pink in center, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

Add tomatoes, mozzarella, and half the dressing to pot with farro and toss. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Slice chicken into strips. Divide farro mixture between plates, then top with chicken. Drizzle with remaining dressing.